  "prompt": "In French, how do you say \"my love\"?",
  "response": "There are several ways to say \"my love\" in French, depending on the context and the person you're addressing:\n\n*   **Mon amour:** This is the most common and versatile translation. It can be used for both men and women.\n\n*   **Ma ch\u00e9rie:** This translates to \"my dear\" or \"my darling\" (feminine). It's used for a woman.\n\n*   **Mon ch\u00e9ri:** This translates to \"my dear\" or \"my darling\" (masculine). It's used for a man.\n\n*   **Mon c\u0153ur:** This translates to \"my heart\" and can be used for both men and women.\n\n*   **Ma bien-aim\u00e9e:** This translates to \"my beloved\" (feminine) and is more formal.\n\n*   **Mon bien-aim\u00e9:** This translates to \"my beloved\" (masculine) and is more formal.\n\nSo, the best option depends on who you are talking to. For general use, **mon amour** is a safe bet.",
